00:14:04.679 --> 00:14:12.280
diversified team. So embrace diversity. It's so obvious, but it's so true. You need to be diverse

00:14:12.280 --> 00:14:20.280
in age, you need to be diverse in gender, and in all of these things that you can be diverse in.

00:14:20.280 --> 00:14:27.719
Because then you bring different mindset into the mix. And I also feel like when you're not

00:14:27.719 --> 00:14:35.880
surrounded by people that are just like you, you automatically become more professional and try to

00:14:35.880 --> 00:14:40.440
bring your A game all the time. That is just something that I think is true. I have no idea

00:14:40.520 --> 00:14:46.919
whether it's true or not. But it's the thing about having different mindsets and don't discriminate

00:14:46.919 --> 00:14:54.840
towards age. Like somebody who's been 30 years in the game is not too old for data science.

00:14:54.840 --> 00:15:01.880
And there's something that I had a discussion on this recently. And I just, in this particular

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:08.760
field, which is this crazy mix of science and thoughts and disciplines and discussions

00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:13.400
and being humane, then I think it's more important than ever to diversify.

00:15:14.599 --> 00:15:22.840
That's just like how I think about things. And one other thing that I'd like to mention is that

00:15:23.559 --> 00:15:33.080
so it's so important to get the sense that you belong to something bigger. And there are

