00:38:26.919 --> 00:38:31.639
I was curious, how do you like prioritise which projects the team works on?

00:38:32.280 --> 00:38:40.439
Yeah, that's a fantastic question. And with an interesting answer. So the data team

00:38:41.399 --> 00:38:46.840
belongs to a bigger department or is a part of a bigger department that is called Department of

00:38:46.840 --> 00:39:00.280
Service and Innovation. So we are tasked with the digital transformation of the city of Reykjavik.

00:39:00.280 --> 00:39:06.360
Basically enhancing and building the digital infrastructure. Not only data and data science,

00:39:06.600 --> 00:39:14.040
but the digital world as a whole. So I would argue that if you're building data products and

00:39:14.040 --> 00:39:20.679
supporting data decision, you're a big part, you play a big supporting part in

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:27.560
the digital transformation journey. So with this digital transformation

00:39:28.280 --> 00:39:34.760
and changes and effort comes a lot of investment. So we are responsible for

00:39:37.159 --> 00:39:44.199
staggering amount of cash. In my mind, in my simple mind, it sounds weird, but it really isn't.

00:39:47.159 --> 00:39:53.639
So the idea is our department is responsible for prioritising projects and person.

00:39:54.600 --> 00:39:59.560
And so we built up this, so we want to do this in a data driven fashion.

00:40:00.360 --> 00:40:09.159
So we built up this, we call it just the matrix. And the matrix has a certain factors in it,

00:40:09.159 --> 00:40:15.479
columns or whatever. And they are like one of the questions that we ask that belong to the matrix,

00:40:15.639 --> 00:40:24.439
how is this bringing value and to whom? And we have certain rating range or a numerical

00:40:25.320 --> 00:40:33.879
range that represents some value. The highest score would be brings a lot of value to employees

00:40:33.879 --> 00:40:39.560
and residents. And we need to be able to articulate that why it's bringing value.

00:40:39.560 --> 00:40:43.879
And that scores something. And then we have other factors that we score by,

00:40:44.360 --> 00:40:50.760
is it supporting the digital infrastructure or is it a hindrance in some way or is it

00:40:51.879 --> 00:41:00.280
alleviating some pain points or whatever. We also have more, so we have like these

00:41:00.280 --> 00:41:08.439
mandates and vision that we work by, like does this correspond to our green initiative.

00:41:08.439 --> 00:41:15.800
And also does this correspond to equality, gender equality and overall embracing diversity

00:41:15.800 --> 00:41:21.800
within a city. We're trying to score, I think if I remember correctly, it's seven categories.

00:41:21.800 --> 00:41:31.000
And they all represent it and the numerical values have some meaning behind them. So when we do this

00:41:31.560 --> 00:41:40.439
rigorously like that, we get like a list of projects that are scored efficiently. And then

00:41:40.439 --> 00:41:49.399
we are in a better position to argue for doing things this way. And since our, like we need to

00:41:49.399 --> 00:41:58.600
be responsible, we need to make the argument for our choices to city council. And so when we do

00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:05.719
this in this data-driven fashion, it's easier to defend your position, if you can think about it

00:42:05.719 --> 00:42:13.560
that way. But it isn't built only for that. It's built for us to understand why we're prioritizing

00:42:13.560 --> 00:42:23.000
projects. And before we built up this procedure, we chose projects into the data team, basically

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:29.560
just like the first year was just being cowboys and just thinking something that was interesting.

00:42:29.560 --> 00:42:35.239
But now we are more rigorous in thinking about, hey, we need to build up a data lake. Hey, we need

00:42:35.239 --> 00:42:43.719
to build up this and data APIs and all of that, such that we can start to, that we can expand and

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:58.280
grow efficiently. So there's more to the story. So the other departments, they also need to

00:42:58.280 --> 00:43:06.040
prioritize their projects before they come into us. And we prioritize them. And this is not only

00:43:06.040 --> 00:43:13.080
data, this is the digital transformation effort as a whole. And how we are, the framework that

00:43:13.080 --> 00:43:19.879
we're building is that we are injecting these teams agents into the other departments and we

00:43:19.879 --> 00:43:28.760
call them digital leaders. And the teams agents or digital leaders, they work closely with the

00:43:28.760 --> 00:43:39.639
department heads and they have a certain mandate to work. And their task is to get an insight into

00:43:39.639 --> 00:43:45.879
the operations of their departments and see opportunities for digital transformation.

00:43:46.679 --> 00:43:52.600
So they are tasked with like getting their hands dirty and trying to find out, hey, here are pain

00:43:52.600 --> 00:43:58.520
points, we can do this, this, this. And then they bring that to us and that goes to the matrix and

00:43:58.520 --> 00:44:06.280
then we start to go and then we go to work. And so it's extremely interesting. And for the past

00:44:06.280 --> 00:44:13.399
half year, for me, it is more like being a part of this digital transformation journey than only

00:44:13.399 --> 00:44:19.000
data science. Data science plays a vital role, but it's just a piece of the puzzle.

