graphs. And you can slice and dice on a dashboard and filter out the data. And then you can download

00:47:03.320 --> 00:47:12.199
the image. Like you can download it as is. Like how it appears. And that was just a game changer

00:47:12.199 --> 00:47:19.560
for somebody. And I had no idea that they didn't realize that. You know there's a download button,

00:47:19.560 --> 00:47:27.320
you can just press it. And this only happens because we talked frequently and you just,

00:47:28.280 --> 00:47:33.639
yeah, I'm not sure whether there's a silver bullet here. But I think the approach is,

00:47:35.479 --> 00:47:44.840
dare I say, humility and realize that nobody thinks the same. And most people have no interest

00:47:44.840 --> 00:47:52.199
in data. I just, if you're okay with that, like that doesn't affect me as a person or my interest.

00:47:52.840 --> 00:47:57.479
I'm just okay with explaining, hey, a linear relationship, that's something that is,

00:47:58.040 --> 00:48:04.760
like looks like that. Hey, Simpson's paradox, did you hear about that? Like, if you're just okay

00:48:04.760 --> 00:48:13.080
with that and also curious about their business, then something can happen. I think the,

